Nigerian Opposition Candidates Shun TV Debate, ThisDay Says

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-03-25T08:51:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/nigerian-opposition-candidates-shun-tv-debate-thisday-says.html
Nigeria ’s opposition presidential
candidates pulled out of a televised debate with President
Goodluck Jonathan scheduled for March 28-29, ThisDay  reported, 
citing a statement by the parties.  Muhammadu Buhari of the Congress for Progressive Change,
Nuhu Ribadu of the Action Congress of  Nigeria , and Ibrahim
Shekarau of All Nigeria Peoples Party, will not participate in
the debate, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  The candidates pulled out in protest at Jonathan’s refusal
to participate in a debate last week organized by NN24 TV,
ThisDay said. Jonathan is the candidate for the ruling People’s
 Democratic Party .  Nigeria, Africa’s most populous nation and leading oil
producer, will hold state, National Assembly, governorship and
presidential elections in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos via Accra at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 